<username>Ali Matin</username><Date>1571260464781< /Date><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
Joe the technician was assigned to help with my plumbing needs. He was very knowledgeable and identified the issue with my clogged toilet drain. He explained the problem was with the cast iron clean out fitting used for construction. The cast iron fitting is rough on the inside and after time, calcium build up can shrink the internal diameter of the fitting. This can promote waste build up. He was able to clear the clog in the pipe, however, I will need to replace the clean out fitting in the near future. Overall my experience with Joe and Roto-Rooter was excellent.<//Text>

< Review>
I called about 6:20am coz when I got a call from the downstairs tenants who were experiencing back-up debris from the upstairs unit.  Obviously, there's urgency if you see feces overflowing from your toilet, which is out of your control.  The Roto Rooter associate (Palmer) told me that the techs are coming in at 8am; she never gave me any other options like using the night service for a fee.  So I  waited until around 9am to follow up; but the associate who answered the call  (I think Vicky) wasn't much of a help.  She just told me that my service request is queued and whoever is available will be assigned.  Mind you this is following up after more than 3 hrs since I placed the call.  At that time, I have decided to call other companies I have dealt with before who were more attentive to send someone with a timeline already, or who was willing to go right after finishing up a job.  Shortly after that follow-up call with Roto Rooter, I was told that Hugo is on his way and about an hour away.  Finally, after almost half of the day is gone just waiting, Hugo finally came.  He is personable, friendly, and seems knowledgeable of his trade.  I explained to him my frustration with the unresponsiveness and lack of attention and compassion to this urgent need.  Although the estimate was higher than what I was charged by another top plumbing company before, I've decided to have the job done considering I dont have much time because it was wasted just waiting to assign this work-order to a tech.  Also, their office is located in Hemet and so the equipment like the camera and the hydrojetting machine was another time wasted waiting.  The job was finally done by 5pm, which I think could have been done effectively and efficiently within 2 hrs.  Though I was sold with using the camera and hydrojetting it just to prevent future issues, the camera was used only for few minutes and taken by the supervisor (Gerry) before the hydrojetting started.  For the fee I paid I shd have gotten a better service, and considering I have a comparison of how the other plumbing company use camera before and after hydrojetting job.  This leaves a bad impression.  There's more I could say, but I'll stop here.

However, I have to say that Roto Rooter's profile of the techs they're sending is impressive.  The cost of it must be factored in the service fee they're charging.‚òπ< /Review>

< Review>
Allan Graber repaired our main water line which had a leak under the driveway as it turned out. It took a considerable amount of digging and chasing just to locate the leak. The original installer took an unconventional route apparently to avoid breaking up several large rocks that Allan had to contend with and remove just to discover the location. Following several trips to Home Depot to acquire the proper fittings and
installation tools, the leak was repaired in short order. The line started out as a one inch copper line from the meter and appeared to end at the home entrance as the same size line. (Not!) It was a PEX  flex line several inches under the driveway. I might add that this was a hot and humid day on July 4th. Despite several large obstacles (Big Rocks!) Alan never complained and got us back in business.<//Review>

<date>1397056841462<//date><Rate>5< /Rate><Text>The phone answerer, Bridgette, asked only a few questions about what needed fixing, a bathtub faucet leaking problem. The questions seemed only relevant to their own need to provide us with a quick response to get the job done well, and within that call she said Roto-Rooter could have a plumber there within an hour. She had a very friendly manner in her voice and personality. I told her many found our residence hard to locate, so advised her to tell the person coming to fix the leaking faucets to call me when he got to the nearest well known street intersection. It was a pleasant surprise to hear his phone call to me within 30 minutes, then I got in my little car and met him to escort the Roto-Rooter truck to our ranch, and our permanent foundation modular house, a Champion made in 1988. Roto Rooter had replaced all of the plastic water pipes circa 1995 with copper pipes and stainless steel flex cables to almost every outlet. This has made the house almost trouble free since then. The plumber arrived smiling and totally ready to go to work. He took apart the ailing old tub valve stems, showed my wife and I how they'd disintegrated over time since the manufacture of the house. He was almost immediately able to come up with an exact price of what the fix would cost. Returning from a run to town to get the parts, he took out a much larger box of tools, and he did the replacing of both valves with brand new ones taking about 15 minutes (he had gone to town to find the somewhat unusual modular house parts). Allen, the plumber, had accepted a root beer I'd given him since the day was so hot, but upon leaving I noticed he had left the big glass half full, so intent he had been upon fixing our problem quickly. He and I worked together to adjust the rubber seals, me turning the house water supply valve on and off quickly for his adjusting in the tub, and my wife even gave him an old grommet she had from where she works that proved helpful. The complete professionalism of Roto-Rooter in doing everything they said they would do, and doing it fast caused me in saying goodby to Allen, "Thanks for the fast fix and the high competence of your work." Working with them was actually fun, since every other plumbers we had called seemed almost afraid of doing modular and mobile home cases.< /Text>< Pictures>

<rate>5< /rate><Text>Had a broker later line in my second home in Hemet. Called "7" plumbers who advertised 24/7 plumbing service. Five of these companies made "excuses" of why they could not come out that night at 12 midnight. The 6th company said they had a man already out in the field and he would not be finished for "at least" 2 hours and it might have to wait till the morning. We called two of the Roto Router Offices trying to locate a plumber and the answering service noted that both of our calls were for the same address (indicating they have a good tracking system), The answering service lady indicated she would call the service man on call and get back to me "shortly" in about 10 minutes. Sure enough ten minutes late Joe T. called and asked questions about the problem, size of the broke pipe (to be sure he had parts in the truck) or he would had to run to the service center to pick up parts. I explain the problem, gave him the measurement of the pipe size (attempted to take a photo but it was too wet and dark even with a flash). He said he would come out and should arrive in about 15 minutes. HE ARRIVED IN 15 MINUTES.
As it turned out Joe T. is the "supervisor" and the man on call was not there and this was the third night in a row that Joe T. went out for somebody else. He was very polite, pleasant, knowledgeable and quick to diagnose the problem. They was a time delay due to my lot unfortunately did not have a water shut off value from the street. An unfortunate complication, we had looked and so did the the subdivision manager and grounds manager before we even called the plumber. So the entire subdivision water had to be shut down. Once that was completed Joe T. Fixed the problem in about 15 minutes. The bill was slightly expense, but for the time of night and quick response, it was "very reasonable". This excellent rating is mainly because of this companies good backup supervisor who really deserves the credit. If he wasn't there for backup, this might be an entirely different review. Yeah Joe T. REALLY GOOD JOB!
So if you call Roto Rooter in Hemet and you can't get the main service guy, be sure to tell them you wish to speak with Joe T.</Text><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< Resp>

<rating>5< /rating>< review>
Champ's Deli also has a catering menu which I ordered from for a Celebration of Life event in Long Beach, Sunday, September 29, 2019. The family chose the pasta bar which I personally have chosen on 2 past occasions. Their pasta bar is always consistently delicious and arrives hot in chafing dishes with gel fuel to keep warm. They always arrive on time and set up everything that's needed and you just call them when you are finished with your event so they can pick up all their equipment. One small detail impressed me greatly : their sliced carrots in their salad were cut into flowers!! Their customer service is 200%. James and Lisa helped me with things that were not even in their job description!!! They also have other selections such as a Japanese bar, Chinese, Mexican, sandwich, Thanksgiving, etc. I have only tasted their pasta bar. Very reasonable pricing per person. You cannot go wrong in choosing Champ's Deli for an event.< /review>

<user>105459799199639198946</user><Name>Storage Dave A Regular Guy< /Name><date>1532107351636<//date><Rating>5<//Rating><Review>This hidden gem in Signal Hill is a great place to stop and have lunch with the family. I ordered the turkey and avocado sandwich, which was delicious with soft bread and lots of turkey. My son had the chicken wrap which they cut up into tiny little circles: he loved it. My wife had the tuna salad which was fresh and crisp. My other son had the chicken teriyaki which comes laid on a bed of soft white rice and an extra cup of teriyaki sauce. We also had some made-from-scratch potato salad and ice cream. Everything was good. The restaurant is clean. They have an all you can drink iced tea station and coffee in the corner, along with a fridge full of canned and bottled beverages that are ice cold. We met the new owners James and Annie, an older Korean couple who have a passion for the business. This new ownership has breathed new life into this Signal Hill restaurant which celebrates its 40th anniversary next year. If you're in the area stop by, I think they also do catering if you have big events or need to order lunch for your entire business. I would definitely recommend this to a friend stopping in for a quick bite to go or anyone wanting to sit down and have a good meal. They have American, Asian, Mexican and all kinds of healthy food.</Review><Pictures>None</Pictures><response>None<//response><GmapID>0x80dd322a0ff3cc8f:0xc5abd7b0a8a1739c</GmapID></record></dataset><record>
